INSERT INTO fitness_tips (tip_id, diet_goal_id, tip) VALUES
(1,  1, 'Increase calorie intake: To build muscle mass, you need to consume more calories than you burn. Your body requires additional energy resources for muscle building and repair.'),
(2,  1, 'Focus on protein: Protein is crucial for muscle growth. Aim to consume an adequate amount of high-quality protein in every meal. Good sources include meat, fish, eggs, dairy products, and legumes.'),
(3,  1, 'Balance your diet: In addition to protein, it is important to consume the right amounts of carbohydrates and fats. Carbohydrates provide energy for your workouts, while fats are essential for various metabolic functions.'),
(4,  1, 'Eat regularly: Try to have smaller, well-balanced meals every 2-3 hours. This will help maintain a steady energy level and provide the necessary nutrients for muscle growth.'),
(5,  1, 'Increase water intake: Proper hydration is vital for health and muscle-building processes. Drink an adequate amount of water throughout the day, especially before, during, and after workouts.'),
(6,  1, 'Choose appropriate exercises: Focus on compound exercises that engage multiple muscle groups simultaneously, such as squats, deadlifts, and bench presses. This allows for greater effectiveness in building muscle mass.'),
(7,  1, 'Increase training intensity: Gradually increase the weight and intensity of your workouts to stimulate muscle growth. Aim to perform exercises with heavier weights or more repetitions as your body develops.'),
(8,  1, 'Prioritize recovery: Muscles grow during rest, so ensure you get enough sleep and allocate sufficient time for recovery between workouts. Overtraining can hinder muscle-building progress.'),
(9,  1, 'Monitor progress: Keep a training journal to track your progress. Record weights, repetitions, and other relevant information. This will help you monitor your progress and adjust your training and diet accordingly.'),
(10, 1,  'Be patient: Building muscle mass is a process that takes time and dedication. Do not expect immediate results. Be consistent, committed, and dedicated to your plan, and results will come gradually.'),
(11, 2, 'Create a calorie deficit: To reduce body fat, you need to consume fewer calories than you burn. Your body will start using stored fats as an energy source.'),
(12, 2, 'Focus on a balanced diet: Choose foods rich in fiber, vitamins, and nutrients, such as vegetables, fruits, whole grains, healthy fats, and lean proteins. Limit the consumption of processed and high-fat foods.'),
(13, 2, 'Avoid empty calories: Limit the intake of sugary beverages, high-calorie snacks, and foods high in saturated and trans fats. Opt for healthier options like water, fresh fruits, vegetables, and low-fat protein sources.'),
(14, 2, 'Increase protein intake: Protein has thermogenic properties and helps maintain satiety. Consume lean sources of protein like poultry, fish, lean meats, eggs, and legumes.'),
(15, 2, 'Increase physical activity: Regular cardio exercises like running, swimming, or cycling help burn calories and reduce body fat. Additionally, strength training helps maintain muscle mass.'),
(16, 2, 'Incorporate interval training: Interval training, which combines intense periods of exercise with shorter recovery periods, is an effective tool for fat burning. Try activities like alternating between sprinting and jogging.'),
(17, 2, 'Reduce consumption of simple carbohydrates: Limit products made from white flour, sugar, sweets, and sugary drinks. Instead, opt for whole grain products with a low glycemic index and rich in fiber.'),
(18, 2, 'Include healthy fats: Limit saturated and trans fats, which are unhealthy for the heart. Choose healthy fats like avocado, olive oil, nuts, seeds, and fatty fish, as they provide essential nutrients.'),
(19, 2, 'Monitor calorie intake: Keep a food diary to track your calorie consumption. Maintain control over the number of meals and portion sizes.'),
(20, 2, 'Be patient and consistent: Fat reduction is a process that takes time. Do not expect immediate results. Stay consistent, stick to your diet and training plan, and results will gradually become visible.'),
(21, 3, 'Balanced diet: Choose a variety of foods from each food group, including vegetables, fruits, whole grains, lean protein, healthy fats, and low-fat dairy products.'),
(22, 3, 'Moderate calorie deficit: Adjust your calorie intake to maintain a balance between the calories you consume and the calories you burn. Avoid extreme calorie restrictions.'),
(23, 3, 'Balanced meals: Aim for balance and proportion in your meals, ensuring they include appropriate amounts of protein, carbohydrates, and fats. Avoid high-calorie snacks '),
(24, 3, 'Regular meals: Have regular and balanced meals throughout the day. Avoid skipping meals and starving yourself, as this can lead to overeating later on.'),
(25, 3, 'Portion control: Be mindful of portion sizes to avoid excessive calorie intake. Use smaller plates and bowls to make the portions appear larger.'),
(26, 3, 'Variety of exercises: Incorporate different forms of physical activity, including cardio, strength training, and interval training. This will help maintain muscle mass, burn calories, and keep your workouts interesting.'),
(27, 3, 'Find enjoyable activities: Engage in physical activities that you enjoy to make exercise a sustainable and enjoyable part of your lifestyle. This could include dancing, swimming, hiking, or playing sports.'),
(28, 3, 'Practice mindful eating: Pay attention to your body hunger and fullness cues. Eat slowly, savor each bite, and listen to your body signals to avoid overeating.'),
(29, 3, 'Stay hydrated: Drink plenty of water throughout the day to maintain proper hydration and support overall health and metabolism.'),
(30, 3, 'Monitor your progress: Keep track of your weight, measurements, and food intake. Regularly assess your progress to make any necessary adjustments to your diet and exercise routine.');